{
  "text": "For the evaluation of brain edema, mice were sacrificed at reperfusion 24 hr after MCAO injury. Brain slices (2 mm thick) between 22.00 mm and +4.00 mm from Bregma were incubated with 2% 2, 3, 5-triphenyltetraxolium chloride (TTC) (SigmaAldrich, St. Louis, MO, USA) at 37\u00b0C for 10 min in the dark in a drying oven, and later photographed using a Nikon E950 digital camera attached to a dissecting microscope. Infarct volume was determined from digitized images using the Quantity One software package (Bio-Rad, CA, USA). Typically 3 such slices were used for analysis. The area of the cortical and striatal infarct was measured separately in all slices in the ischemic and non-ischemic hemisphere. The ipsilateral and contralateral hemispheres were used to calculate the percentage of brain edema [CITATION_1] .",
